"title": "5072: Aaron, spokesman for Moses",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5072: aaron, spokesman for moses",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>He was called by God to speak for his brother Moses in the confrontation with Pharaoh and to lead the Israelites out of Egypt. Negligence of the LORD's express command cost him the privilege of entering the promised land.</p>\n<h2>Aaron's genealogy and family</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:20\">EXO 6:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:1-Lev10:3\">LEV 10:1–10:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:1-Num3:2\">NUM 3:1–3:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:3\">1CH 6:3</a></p>\n<h2>Aaron was spokesman for Moses in Egypt</h2>\n<h3>His call</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:14-Exod4:16\">EXO 4:14–4:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The brothers meet and confront Pharaoh</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod5:1\">EXO 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:27-Exod4:28\">EXO 4:27–4:28</a></p>\n<h3>The command to lead the Israelites out of Egypt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:13\">EXO 6:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Aaron's staff</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:8-Exod7:12\">EXO 7:8–7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:19-Exod7:20\">EXO 7:19–7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:5-Exod8:6\">EXO 8:5–8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:16-Exod8:17\">EXO 8:16–8:17</a></p>\n<h3>Pharaoh's hardness of heart</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:10\">EXO 11:10</a></p>\n<h2>Subsequent events in Aaron's life</h2>\n<h3>The LORD's instructions for the Passover</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:43\">EXO 12:43</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:1-Exod12:3\">EXO 12:1–12:3</a></p>\n<h3>The Israelites grumble against Moses and Aaron</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:2-Exod16:3\">EXO 16:2–16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:9\">EXO 16:9</a></p>\n<h3>Aaron commemorates the LORD's provision of manna</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:33\">EXO 16:33</a></p>\n<h3>The meeting of Aaron and Jethro</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:12\">EXO 18:12</a></p>\n<h3>Aaron as census-taker</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:3\">NUM 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:34\">NUM 4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:46\">NUM 4:46</a></p>\n<h3>Aaron as prayer partner</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:10\">EXO 17:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:12\">EXO 17:12</a></p>\n<h3>Aaron's jealousy and subsequent repentance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:1-Num12:2\">NUM 12:1–12:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:5\">NUM 12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:11\">NUM 12:11</a></p>\n<h3>Aaron makes the people a golden calf</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:4\">EXO 32:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:1-Exod32:3\">EXO 32:1–32:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:5\">EXO 32:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:40\">ACT 7:40</a></p>\n<h3>Moses rebukes him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:21-Exod32:24\">EXO 32:21–32:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:35\">EXO 32:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:20\">DEU 9:20</a></p>\n<h3>Rebellion against Moses and Aaron</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:2\">NUM 14:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:3\">NUM 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:11\">NUM 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:20-Num16:22\">NUM 16:20–16:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:39-Num16:48\">NUM 16:39–16:48</a></p>\n<h3>Aaron's authority vindicated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:8\">NUM 17:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num17:10\">NUM 17:10</a></p>\n<h3>The LORD prevents Aaron and Moses from entering the promised land</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:2\">NUM 20:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:7-Num20:12\">NUM 20:7–20:12</a></p>\n<h2>The death of Aaron</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:25-Num20:26\">NUM 20:25–20:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:28-Num20:29\">NUM 20:28–20:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:38-Num33:39\">NUM 33:38–33:39</a></p>",
